data.title: Reverberations Session 1
data.description:
Archived on 2025-09-07, this archive contains 1032 messages between 9:57:03 PM to 2:33:01 AM.
					It has 11 dice rolls.

messages.content: Reverberations
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A game about spiralling down.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to Mexico City. We have just arrived at Benito Juárez International Airport. The local time is approximately 3:57 PM, and the temperature outside is 25 °C (77 °F). For your safety, please remain seated with your seatbelt fastened until the aircraft has come to a complete stop and the captain has turned off the seatbelt sign. At this time, you may use your mobile phones, but please keep your carry-on items stowed until it is safe to retrieve them. On behalf of United Airlines and this entire crew, thank you for flying with us today. We wish you a pleasant stay here in Mexico City or safe travels to your final destination."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your Xanax induced haze comes to an end as the flight attendant prods you awake, asking for you to fasten your seatbelt.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That was the last of the evidence locker freebies.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The plane is packed with people, as usual. A woman next to you buckles her seatbelt.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Señoras y señores, bienvenidos a la Ciudad de México. Hemos llegado al Aeropuerto Internacional Benito Juárez. La hora local es aproximadamente 15:57 y la temperatura exterior es de 25 °C (77 °F). Por su seguridad, les pedimos que permanezcan sentados con el cinturón de seguridad abrochado hasta que la aeronave se haya detenido por completo y el capitán apague la señal de cinturones. En este momento pueden utilizar sus teléfonos móviles, pero por favor mantengan su equipaje de mano guardado hasta que sea seguro retirarlo. En nombre de United Airlines y de toda la tripulación, les agradecemos por volar con nosotros hoy. Les deseamos una agradable estancia en la Ciudad de México o un buen viaje hacia su destino final."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon jolts awake and looks around momentarily, before fiddling with the seatbelt while muttering something to himself. With a click, he lets his hands loose at his sides and reclines back in the seat, as if expecting it to swallow him.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: How the fuck did you end up here? You don't recall a thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can see Finnegan from here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And you turn your head to see Earle, fiddling with his phone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your brain is still too hazy. The chattering of people and kids melts into the cabin brown noise.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Fuck, I must've asked for whiskey again," he thinks to himself as he bangs his head back against the seat once and sighs.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The woman next to you giggles and returns to her Blackberry.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What are the others doing from where you sit?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle. Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You remember it now. There are more, actually. It's just that you can only see these two.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It looks like Finnegan is studying his notes. For Earle…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Absorbed in his phone, watching some episodes of Dallas he downloaded in preparation for the flight. He's visibly nervous and hasn't said a word all flight.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: He seems just fine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your teeth stop clenching and feeling returns back to your hands. You start recalling the recent events all the way from start.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A basketball court…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: LOADING.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're at the right place, at the right time. Or so you hope. Actually, you've been standing there for 5 minutes now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The cigarette is in your pocket. What do you do?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I check my watch. Again. I scrutinize the cigarette - again. I'll give it another five minutes. Round up.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Between the distant traffic, you can hear two cars pull up outside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A man disembarks first.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And a woman. Two women, actually.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A couple other guys get off too.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All are feds from a mile away. No one shows up here in a business suit. They are your kind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The foremost guy seems to be holding a rolled up folder.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Thank God. This building was starting to make me nervous. You can feel the mold in the air.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You dust yourself off and calmly wait for them to enter the court from that door right there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The guy opens the door for others and begins walking towards you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You are holding a NDA and other papers to sign this person into the //SSG clearance. He doesn't seem to object to it, so far.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may move.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon walks towards Finnegan, mostly looking around at the ceiling, and as he gets closer he turns his head to him, but the look is as if he's looking through glass.  He's transparent to him.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan. You instantly recognize the lady. The others, well…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're barely in Washington and you have not seen them around your floor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
Well, it's a big small community, like they say.

"Good morning, everyone."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "And a good five PM morning to you, Mr. Finnegan."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin nods.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: McCannon stands directly in front of Finnegan, face to face. Then he looks him up and down, folder at his side.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Morning.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: IT'S FIVE O'CLOCK.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: CLOCK TO BOTTOM LEFT.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He pulls a pen from his front jacket pocket, as he pulls up the folder to his chest level and opens it up.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Everyone is standing there expecting you to get it over with. Of course, you have the free will to object.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He shuffles the NDA up first, pulls out the paper and hands it to Finnegan. "The rest of your life is on this paper. Think before you put the ink to paper." He clicks the pen and hands it aswell.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "He's had plenty of time to think, Agent McCannon."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: This is my chance. Finally. My signature is tight and neat, like a carbon-copy stamp on every document I ink.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon turns his head to Diaz: "It's never enough time, unfortunately."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: McCannon turns back to Finnegan and pulls out more pages as he collects the ones he has signed already.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
The pen makes a scrubbing noise as it dances on top of archival grade paper.

Here, here, here, and you're done. Fifteen seconds of constant signing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Then he closes the folder shut and nods.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: All the while SA Doug Moore is doing his best impression of the Ceilings and Floors Observation Team Duty Officer.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "I'm glad you made the right choice, Agent Finnegan. We should get started right now, sooner the better."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Goes without saying, everything here, beyond classified. It's not just your badge that's in line anymore."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She clears her throat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"We are here today for the briefing on Operation Chokecherry."

She corrects her hair and produces a singular, unmarked manila folder from her leather bag.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon steps back and gets into the semicircle.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: She hands the folder out to McCannon, to pass it along.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Of course there'd never be copies of this. Figures…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon passes the briefing folder to Doug. "Pass it when you're done."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "You're holding the death warrant of two gangsters and their friends. The stuff they deal goes beyond the usual coke and molly all of us love to do a bump of."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We believe that high level corruption is involved in the making of this… situation."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug takes in the the contents of the file, parsing the legalese into actual statements. Despite that, the "OBJECTIVES" are clear as they can be.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Done. Here, Frank." And he passes the folder on
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "We are the ones who are going to clean it up. Whether the district federal judge likes it or not."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hundreds of thousands of lives are in immediate danger."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Study the document and line up your questions. Piss intermission.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He scans the files and the further he gets wider his eyes grow. "Holy shit." He deadpans. "Fuckin'… Fu Manchu…"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: He passes the files to Samantha.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Cliff holds the file in the same hand as her cigarette, juggling between shifting pages and taking a drag. She looks focused as she reads. Afterwards, she gives the file to Vasmin with a nod.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin accepts the dossier from Samantha and starts parsing it.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin rapidly shuffles his eyes up and down the document in a mechanical manner, repeating this routine three times, before passing the file to Richard Finnegan.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Finnegan looks, reads, and comprehends. He's full of questions, but he looks expectantly at Diaz for a cue.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Diaz is fiddling with a worn out zippo. You can tell pretty easily what she is going to use it for.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We've gotta be dealing with some maniacs if the drug running is only the cover…
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Quotations for talking, please.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Tong. Tong… Shuriken. And Chen and Feng and…", Moore mutters under his breath. Clearly, the Oriental overtones of the operation might be tough to navigate around. Doug does not speak up about it, not just yet.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin looks at Frank and nods solemnly, shoots a glance out the window, then looks expectantly at Richard.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Those two reduced a life sentence to a conditional release. You better get their names right before you show up on their doorstep."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "…Shukoran." He says it with the correct inflection.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I'm taking that your lack of questions stem from the fact that this operation is not just utterly unconstitutional but illegal as well."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Unfortunately for you, there is no backpedalling now."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If you weren't aware of it so far welcome to the game."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug shoots a glance at the others. It works as well as anything for a display of agreement.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The game: Noun. Activities of an intelligence community.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan tightens his lips and makes a conciliatory nod.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Right. Let's get down to the meat and potatoes."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff returns Moore's glance with a light nod.
messages.author: YZosE7uqfWlBpjlI

messages.content: "You are going to insert into the operation zone over Mexico."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "All of you, as of last night, are signed off on a classified JTTF assignment to our sister location in Mexico City. Of course, you'll never show up there."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You have plane tickets book for this Sunday. You're going to take a chartered Cessna prop plane to Chiuhaua International from Benito Juarez and make the rest of trip by land with the help of our assets."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They will arrive in DEA costume."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A funny choice of words.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They'll take you up to El Paso and drop you off at your vehicle cache."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Thereon, it should be a 4 hour drive to Albuquerque."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The land of enchancement, so to speak."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: So many locations and names and plots. Doug finds himself wishing for the first time that the others are as competent as he thinks himself to be.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Your IDs are the real thing until the end of next week. Then, all of your computerized information will be wiped out before the routine backup, making scrutiny impossible."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You should consider dying before getting caught out there in a DEA windbreaker holding a fake badge. That's why you should wrap it up before Sunday noon."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That being said, try not to get shot. We'll have to pull you out of a hospital at best, and at worst… actually let's not go there."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle's been nervously touching his face for a while now as he pictures the torture he'll be subjected to if these triads get a hold of him.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "ASAC Schrader of ABQ DEA has been briefed on the arrival of a task force from El Paso to investigate the, quote unquote, sudden uptick of trade volume in drugs."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon has been head-up staring at the ceiling the whole time.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "He's not a little kid so clearly he must believe he is under internal investigation scrutiny. You're free to fit your legend any way you like to make it work. I think hundred-mile long tunnels are a funny conversation starter."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Legend: noun. A cover story
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hundred-mile tunnels like what?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "I don't have to say it again, but they must be kept in the dark. You'll have to make reports to him eventually, just bullshit him. Tell him it's the Pistolas. Tell him anything but the fucking truth."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Like the freedoms road, Agent. Tried and true method."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ah, I see."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: It would make for quite a legend indeed.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Something more like a Ho Chi Min trail." Finnegan mutters under his breath.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin huffs slightly.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "I'm sure he knows about the enterpreneurial activities of our southern neighbors," he says to the ceiling.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Right. Once we're established on that, no witnesses or survivors."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The air chills. She clearly means fellow federal agents.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Just about the last thing Doug wanted to hear. After all of this. "No witnesses" is Standard Operating Procedure. 'No survivors', however…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Has an entirely different ring to it
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "We lost two agents and a cop to these pricks in a gunfight. They are armed and extremely, beyond your wildest dreams dangerous."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Any questions I can answer?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Is there any reason for us to believe that they might have some associates in the area involved in the previous tong operation, stateside? More faces and names to look out for, I mean."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "They are in kahoots with Las Pistolas. This side of the border of Sinaloa."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You'll most likely find street to lieutenant level dealers who are hispanic."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Might be the time to break the question. "Uh, Assistant Director?" Doug opens up. "Any possibility we are to agree on some kinds of… code words, for important persons related to the Operation?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Ones that aren't in China Mandarin, or whatever they speak."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "I don't care, Agent. Your tradecraft is yours. By next week I want to call them by the name 'Dead Meat' and 'Rot in Hell'."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "As you wish."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug is already working out the names in his head. "Dragon", "Lance". Yeah, much better.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "That's a keeper," he mutters at the ceiling, once again.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Click, click. Click, click. She is flicking the Zippo cap like a toy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I can't believe this." Earle muttered, exasperated sounding. "We've got the Ming Dynasty slinging dope in Big Rock Candy Mountain." His mind has been very active picturing filigree palaces, dark oriental magic, martial artists with swords and qipao. To say he felt out of his depth would be an understatement.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Anyone confident in their HUMINT, roll. First come first serve.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: A sudden tightening of the atmosphere in the room. Strange.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: David. She is clearly as stressed as you are about this. When you think about it, the whole thing is fucking insane. But, you gotta put food on the table, right.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I like to think about flying swords too, but it's been a century since Samuel Colt made all men equal in war."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin nods solemnly, then intones, "Regarding the eventual collection of the… substance itself, are we to dispose of it on the field- or would that posit some sort of hazard?"
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "You'll find a cache of weapons."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon cracks his neck shoulder to shoulder as he shudders and finally decides to take a look over at the semi-circle, eyes resting on each person for a moment.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "We don't know the exact specific methods of production but the last raid did not result in catastrophic contamination, still, won't hurt to put on some PPE once you come around to setting it on fire."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That bad?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "It means there's been worse."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: A pointless remark. But it came out before Doug could put it away.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin states, "One must then assume that the superiors are not interesting in collecting any samples."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "It's bad, because they refused to tell how to make a brand new drug in front of the god damn state prosecutor."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We're not interested in studying smack."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So, are we done? I gotta make it to a meeting soon."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin nods.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "That's all for me. Are we going to get a more complete record on these two gentlemen when we get there?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: SA Doug Moore nods as well. Talk, as they say, is cheap; and time as of recent had been unusually expensive.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: She scratches her neck awkwardly.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I think you're gonna have to wheel this one out, Agent. Records…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle looks like he's about to say something just to bide the time but he stops himself. Then he nods.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "It's complicated."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: McCannon's face shifts, uncomfortably - more so for the others. "I'm sure Assistant Director has briefed you regarding standard procedure if an agent is….. 'compromised' by 'forces extreme and extraordinary'?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: McCannon turns to face Diaz: "Too soon?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: She interrupts.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Let's not kill the mood. This meeting is adjourned."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We have a seat for you, Agent Finnegan."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What an awful, awful euphemism. Doug does not even stop to consider -- the fact that they're all here means each person in the hall has ran into some of these 'forces'. Probably. Quite likely.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon has a wicked smile, but sad eyes: "They'll learn," he thinks to himself.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: She stares daggers into you and waits for Finnegan's response.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well… We'll see you Monday, then."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Sunday, actually. You're all booked on the same flight."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I take it that you came here with your car. I didn't think that one was yours outside."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, then."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She flips the Zippo open and casually sets the briefing document on fire.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ashes to ashes, dust to dust" he breathes to himself as he drags his foot on the paneling.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The stink of burnt paper reaches your nose. Once it's gone right up until her hand, she drops it into one of the puddles and tramples it a few times.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan watches it go up in cinders wistfully. A lot more dramatic than a government-approved classified-material-compliant cross-shredder.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug side-eyes McCannon. What a strange turn of phrase.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "This meeting never happened and we don't know eachother, Agents."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Have a good day."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The smell of whatever indelible ink just went up in flames makes Doug cough uncomfortably.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Everyone is leaving, unless someone wants to stand around for whatever reason.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Good day, then, Assistant Director."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon starts moving towards the door, opening and propping it with his foot.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The sooner I get out of this building, the better. Whatever's percolating in the drywall is making me queasy.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You're fuckin' weird." He says to Michael with no particular emotion before leaving.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: The start of a wonderful friendship. He sits shotgun in the same car as you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Enjoy the rest of your day, Assistant Director."
Vasmin makes to leave.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: McCannon chuckles to himself.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Moving on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Dulles International Airport, D.C. International Outbound Terminal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Despite the representation you see right now, the weather is quite beautiful today. Briefly describe how you wait for your flight, back in 3 minutes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is sitting on the bed of an errant luggage cart, twiddling with his fingers.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan pays an airport premium price for National Geographic. The cover plainly says 'CHINA' in white letters on a red background. He scrutinizes every photograph and each editorialized diatribe like it's a work document.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug Moore is sort of there, in the background, as present as a mayfly in the summer. He's checking something out on his phone, whether it's related to the Operation at hand or of a different subject entirely no one knows but he.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: But let everyone hope related it is.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin looks over Finnegan's shoulder and nodds appreciatively at the asiatic beauties pictured on the catalog.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Earle is slouched against the only free chair he could find - shirt untucked - thinking back tothe movie he watched before this trip, The 36th Chamber of Shaolin, and chuckling occasionally.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: They're hosting the Olympics this year. The Yangtze's history takes up two whole pages. Optimistic graphs and tables project good outcomes from the ever-growing financialization of the Chinese economy.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
“Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen. We are now ready to begin boarding United Airlines flight 821 with service to Mexico City, Benito Juárez International Airport.

At this time, we would like to invite our premium cabin customers, MileagePlus Premier members, and passengers requiring extra assistance to board.

We will then continue boarding by group number as shown on your boarding pass. Please have your boarding pass and travel documents ready, and remember that each passenger is allowed one carry-on bag and one personal item. Larger carry-on items should be placed in the overhead bins, while smaller personal items should be stored under the seat in front of you.

We kindly ask that you step aside once you have scanned your boarding pass to avoid crowding the gate area.

Once again, this is United Airlines flight 821 with service to Mexico City, Benito Juárez International Airport. We look forward to welcoming you on board, and thank you for choosing United Airlines.”
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Time to go.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon stands up with a groan and produces a boarding pass from his inner jacket pocket as he shuffles towards the gate unenthusiastically.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The sudden feeling that you might not be coming back hits all of you like a punch to the throat.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Did any of you actually realize what is about to unfold?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He hears the music. It's time to dance.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Ignorance is bliss, they say. Here comes Mexico.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The first day of the rest of our lives. Give or take however much life we have left.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: It's not a bad airport. Finnegan will miss it, if he never sees it again. There's always something to appreciate about an airport that isn't bad.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You heard some nice things about Benito Juarez too.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 4 hours later.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. It looks like you're back on the track as soon as you grab your luggage off the luggage claim.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You all fast track through the customs. No one here dares to even fucking question an American federal agent.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon extends the handle and stands the Samsonite case on it's wheels.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Your connecting chartered flight is in an hour.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Luckily, you have two fluent Spanish speakers on board.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's whistling to himself as he goes through the motions of every airport in existance post-9/11
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You make it past the terminal and into the hangars.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hi, are you the dude we are supposed to take to Chihuahua?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A guy, clearly waiting for six sharply dressed federal goons like yourselves, shows up and asks this very question.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug suddenly gets an onset of headache. Probably time for the pills.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
SA David Grozze Vasmin yawns as he emerges out into the hot mexican air. Checking his belongings and ensuring nothing has gone missing- knowing the sort of folks that traipse this territory- he proceeds to disembark along with the rest.

Enjoying the mexican airport tunes, he is suddenly met with the mexican guy.

He says, "Yes. We are the ones you have been expecting."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Si, hermano."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Oooookkay! Come fly with my jet set plane maaan!!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: This guy is very Mexican.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And you just said that to him in English.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Come on ese!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Tone down the paisano and turn on the professional, if you would so kindly."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin says, "Yes, brother- You seem like a man of great skill- lead the way."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: I typed the last two sentences with Spanish selected? Was it working?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: This -is- him being professional, you'd say that the way he talks he probably doesn't know past A2 grade English.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle can't hold back his laughter anymore and has to turn away.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: I don't think you have spanish selected from the dropdown menu.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle pushes Finnegan past the point of professionalism and he hides his mouth with a fist, turning a snicker into a cough.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: This should not be how the Operation is starting. But, this is how the Operation is starting.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: I have it selected right now.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Very well. The guy takes your luggage on board by himself as you make yourselves comfortable.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Next stop: Chiuhaua International.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Any objections?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: None.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: None at all.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: That just worked, Khoka
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Whatever you did tell it to him over Discord, we are moving on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Another 4 hours later, Chihauha International Airport.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The sun is beginning to set. McCannon, you handed the guy a twenty dollar bill as a tip for the jokes he made on the way here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: All of you, your ears are still ringing from the rumbling propellers.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 'Chee-wah-wah'? Doug never heard the name spoken out loud before, much less by a native speaker. There's just no way it's the same as that breed of dog… is it?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: It is.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: For a small town, the airport is quite modern too.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Must be some kind of hub.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Light rain begins to fall.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You're telling me you don't know one of the best destinations for whoring and debauchery in all of Americas, Doug?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Aside from Tijuana."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "I hear if a Mexican likes you they call you caballero." He says to nobody in particular.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "Not into that.", Doug speaks to put the small talk out before anything happens. He knows about Tijuana, though. He knows.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Dalmatians come from Dalmatia. It's the same idea, I think."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "When a Mexican likes an arch-gringo like you that'll be the day."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You guys seem to start getting along despite knowing eachother for just a few hours. That's cute.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Imminent danger and threat of death tends to do that.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: On that topic, Doug and Cliff recognized eachother before as they both work in CID. The rest of you, perhaps brushed against eachother but no dice on telling names.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Now, back to the issue at hand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You were told to wait at the terminals until your guys show up.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon absentmindedly looks at his watch.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You already waited an hour here. Few footsteps clatter in the wide space.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's about nine o'clock local time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Evening?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Affirm.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If only there was a way to tell.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan makes sure to adjust his watch accordingly.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Any other actions than waiting for who knows how long?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're all sitting around, splayed, some in groups.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is going to look around for a vending machine selling the famed 'Mexican Coke'.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin surreptitiously monitors the crowds for any noticeable arrivals.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You find one effortlesly. Only to realize you have no pesos on you, and it's the year 2008 so no card pay here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Maybe a guy is willing to take USD.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon tries to flag a person down for 'ghetto ForEx'
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Handler, is it intentional that we're all in the lobby while only Cliff and McCannon are… tokens?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: It's my laziness, yes, you're all in the same scene.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It doesn't matter.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let us speak no more of that, then.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: SA David Grozze Vasmin notices Michael look helplessly at the vending machine and checks his wallet for any mexican currency.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Yes ese?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You looking to get some dollars, guey?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Oh yeah."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I need enough pesos for a coke. How about I trade you a fiver and you give me just enough, keep the difference, no?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Ehhh let me see what I got."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He is two dollars short but he has a bunch of fucking coins.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Mccannon pulls out a fiver from his wallet.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "You bet!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is just a seat behind from Sam. He admires her hair, maybe without exactly meaning to. All this Mexican speech might well be hieroglyphics to him.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Transaction concludes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Stuff those in there and push the button and here's the five."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Muchas gracias."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "All that for a coke..?"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You achieve your dreams of tasting Mexican Coke.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It tastes like… Coca Cola but kind of Dr. Pepper? It's a little… off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Typea guy to go to a foreign country, go to the McDonald's first thing."
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Care to share?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You walk into a shop with a lathe and ask the guy with a Hulk Hogan beard if you can do a custom request. Once he realizes you're talking about a gun part, he tells you to get the fuck out before calling the cops.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You could try again later.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: For now, your time remains wasted.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sucks, but what can you do. He spends the rest of his time looking into nearby cheap eats before getting a nap.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Hell, you damn well find one.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Los Pollos Hermanos
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You have a pretty alright Peri Peri chicken menu and head back to the safehouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can visit it with the rest of the team later.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Continuing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: DEA ABQ Field Office, Simms Building
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A historical relic, this piece of brutalist architecture has been standing over 50 years in this exact spot.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your access is not questioned whatsoever. The whole cell, sans Earle are standing at the lobby.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Employees are walking about. It's not that full, but there is some activity.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What now?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon will take the lead and ask the receptionist if ASAC Schrader is in.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Right. Please hold."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Third floor."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She goes back to her phone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He nods and motions with his head for others to follow as he makes his way to the elevator.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Fuck the stairs.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Doug could fall on his knees in praise right now. FUCK the stairs, indeed.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He doesn't.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You're at the third floor. Before long, a guy looking for you appears.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Hope you remember your assumed identities fellas.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"Hey you. Are you the guys from El Paso?"

He is talking to Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What rank would I be in the DEA scheme of things? At least for this legend.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Special Agent.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan extends his hand. "Callahan. Rob Callahan. Good to meet you."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan extends his hand. "Callahan. Rob Callahan. Good to meet you."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan extends his hand. "Callahan. Rob Callahan. Good to meet you."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You don't have to talk in your fake names, we just assume you are saying them out loud.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Yeah, Gomez."

He takes out his flip phone and speed dials someone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, Hank. They're here. Alright. Okay."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He flips it back shut.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He'll see you guys in the conference room in ten minutes."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No handshake prick. Finnegan gives him an icy New England smile and nods assent.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Vasmin will try to analyze how this person is reacting.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Does he seem defensive?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: DEA guys are famous for being so chill. He doesn't really give a fuck whether you are here or not.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In any case, you are led to the conference room.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon takes a polite position at the table, probably the nearest at the door so he can get the first handshake in.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's all about them handshakes.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Assume your seats.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It takes about twenty minutes for him to show up. You can see him and Gomez from before out the glass panel.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Time's fucking wasting.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: They are laughing about something, perhaps joking around.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No wonder they let those two guys out without so much as a slap on the wrist. Someone's been sloppy.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Confusion seems afoot. The 2005 raid did not happen in ABQ. You don't know where it exactly happened since you did not bother digging into files before exiting D.C.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: However, sometime somewhere shit went down and these guys don't seem involved with it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A rotund, bald man walks in.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Do they know about the triad activity here?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Hey fellas, welcome to Duke City!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They are the fucking DEA of course they know about asian gangs.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Well,"

He puts his hands together.

"Let's get started with names first."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon stands up to extend a handshake: "SA Jacob Woods."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Doug does likewise: "SA Richard Fell. It's a pleasure."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
"tleast it's not Dookie City, hah."

"SA Kyle Smith. "
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: McCannon cannot believe he said that.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The measure of 'mood' in the room plummets like a stock graph during the Great Depression.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He just grins and lets out an ugly laugh at your extremely childish remark
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan is obviously overthinking Gomez and the handshake, frowning. "Callahan."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Right, then. What's the scoop from El Paso?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Here we got the usual, Sinaloa, ecstasy, meth, you know."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's a pile of shit but it's our pile of shit."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 'DEA suspects methamphetamine', recalls Doug. He's just thinking it, but it helps to think.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
He cracks into laughter again at that.

"I know right, we have some real geniuses spread around the whole nation."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I almost thought it was just candy cigarettes."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, it's actually the usual but with a twist. The task force was set up with regards to the increasing prevalance of Asian-American crime. "
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: His snarky grin stops.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The higher ups are not happy at the appearance of Chinese-Mexican fusion cuisine, if we're speaking metaphorically."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You truly captured his interest.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He is staring at you now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What do you know about triad activities in New Mexico, ASAC Schrader?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Um, actually. It has been a while since we dug into that skin color as a discussion topic."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Dime a dozen street level dealers but anything bigger than that… a rare catch."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Do you read any news about anything south of Mexico?" Finnegan interjects. "Venezuela, for example."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Well I tend to make the news, so."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He grins.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So you're familiar with the reality of how many tons of Chinese freight get into the neighborhood. I think as time goes on, we'll just see more and more of this. Comes with the territory."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He doesn't respond to that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Go on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's probable that some new cooperative enterprises have worked their way up into New Mexico, like he said."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He adjusts his glasses. "They're taking advantage of customs at Latin ports, in other words, and seem to be integrating very well with organized crime with interests here in the States."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
He reclines back in his chair and scratches his chin.

"Well actually, there is this one character we just couldn't fit anywhere in the puzzle a month ago."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Some kid named… shit what was his name… 'Spider' I think. Illegal immigrant but not Mexican, I think he was uh…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't remember. Anyway, we just couldn't link him to a supplier and he was dealing ecstasy out of nowhere. Then one day, poof, the guy is gone."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Not gone gone, but as in vanished without a trace."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well as you said, the topic of race hasn't been in discussion precisely because it has been a done deal. The two colors known for the meth trade at the southern border have been barrio brown and trailer park white."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Much too correct, as some would note.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Personally?" he points to himself with his thumb, "I don't care what color the guy is. A dope slinger is a dope slinger and we're fighting the war on drugs, right?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Meth's the enemy, doesn't matter who is spreading it."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Come on Agent, cut the horse shit. Let me think."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Let me get you a copy of that missing persons report we filed for him."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It'd be much appreciated."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He didn't actually have any family but they just let us go through the process."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That'd be a good  start, actually. Thanks a ton."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "The ABQ PD I mean."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Was he under surveillance?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
He takes out his Motorola flip phone.

"Yeah, Gomie. Can you bring me that poster copy of that Spider guy we were onto last month? Yeah. Okay."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He was."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Were they just watching a location and then one day he never came out?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "We thought it was just some new Pistolas lieutenant but the guy turned out to have no connection to the cartel proper."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Something like that actually. It's a night club. He was preying on there and we were gonna send some agents to entrap him into selling."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "But then one day he spirits away."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You mean to tell me the guy was pushing independent on cartel turf?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "I mean what the hell is that guys."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Seemingly so."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He'd be skinned alive before he could say 'Por favor no'"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "That's why we had intel look into his every last detail, we thought he was Pistolas."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's strange. Maybe he cut some kind of deal? Ehh I don't know. Probably selling to teenagers in hell as we speak."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Gomez brings a folder in front of Schrader and leaves the room immediately.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, we'd see it if they got to him. They like sending a message, don't they?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "We'd better hope so."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Here you go."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't hope so. We still need to slap the shit out of him and see what's up before he goes to hell."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Realistically, and I don't mean to spark anyone's imagination, there's a serious chance he's in a 55-gallon drum somewhere in the Chihuahuan." Finnegan reaches for the poster.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "The thing about the cartel is, if you fuck them they will fuck you one hundred times hard. I didn't think his death would go so under the radar."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "How long ago was this, specifically?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Give or take a month."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What is that? A Persian? Weird haircut for an asian." He tries to make it out leaning over the table looking at the poster.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan pushes it towards McCannon. "I assume the exact date and time is written down in the full police report."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yeah the resolution is soggy. We don't know what breed of Asian, apparently he dodged ICE ever since he came to the States."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Bush in office and ICE still hasn't got it's shit together."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Whatever, the way it's filed you gotta go sweet talk the PD into giving it out to you. We didn't admit into placing him under surveillance."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Much cleaner this way." He winks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Task forces can get away with a lot."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan nods. "Right. What about the club?" He narrows it down. "Who's going there? College kids, gangbangers?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It's a rave club. Mostly young adults, but some well dressed Hispanic figures may be around."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The owner got shot and did some time inside if I recall correctly. He repented ever since, though. Claims to be 'clean'."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Interesting." He means it, sincerely.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "We'll have to get some more information about who's into it on paper. It might make things a little more transparent."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He's clean, club ain't."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "The usual schtick."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Who is into what?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The business. Registered owners. Just small potatos. I like to start there."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yeah well, figure it out. It's just one guy."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If that's all then maybe it's time for us to go home."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The name of the place would be appreciated."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Uhhhm…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I was about to say."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "It's called… something Overground."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I don't remember the first part."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Just Google it, agent."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That narrows it down enough."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He gets up and gets the folder.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well it's certainly been interesting meeting you folks."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm looking forward to your report."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: These boneheads should have more to turn over than this. I'm glad I didn't go to the DEA table at the job fair.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "We'll start digging and reconvene when we hit something actionable."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "So far it's smoke and mirrors, but we've got a start."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: It's one dealer who went missing a month ago. He's not even Hispanic. He thinks he's dead, because what else could he be.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He has a field office to run, ya know.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Things start turning up when you start looking for them.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Unless you interrupt, you will begin exchanging handshakes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon stands up and goes through the motions of professional farewells.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finally, a decent handshake.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug shakes hands last and walks out last.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Vasmin does the requisite hand shakes.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: And so it was.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Once Schrader steps out, Finnegan is ready to make a plan.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Hank waves a formal-ish bye and goes about his business.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The time is…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What's the next move?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He looks at McCannon. "I'd like to take the lead on local PD."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Sure, take someone with you so you don't look weird walking around without a partner."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He looks over at Vasmin.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Federal agents mostly work alone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It doesn't matter.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Mostly, but we're a task force.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "They're going to get our foot in the door. Not only do they have hard copies of any black-and-white we want…" He gestures for effect. "Any regular cop we can pin down into some friendly smalltalk is going to know about the club."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Finding out what the club is actually called and where it's located would be a… sensible first step."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: List your actions. Earle, you're still having dinner so we are skipping you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon will be googling local clubs ABQ.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Uh, where exactly?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Over which computer
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Find a library or some shit.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Enjoy taxpayer dollars at work.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Finnegan plans on heading to the APD station to introduce himself to the desk sergeant and "gather information".
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You manage to find an unoccupied and unlocked computer inside Simms.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Local Clubs Albuquerque Overground. Dozens of results, but, of the same thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Studio Overground.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No other club shares this name.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Bingo.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Think of what to do afterwards. The group is all split up, so you don't think showing up alone in your jorts is gonna be very fruitful to the whole process.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug and David, actions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is quite at a lack of anything to do and rest would be a priority right now, if permissible.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: I get a camera and a recorder from somewhere.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: That is, a voice recorder.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You did not book the motel yet, you either do that or take a cab to the safehouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A question not related to anything and very much said in jest:
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: David, you manage to find both in a pawn shop for cheap. They are of incidental expense.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: How would a fine gentleman acquire stuff needed to make homemade explosives in ABQ?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: DEA Armory or farm supply store
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I purchase the goods.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: or something more creative
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Add them to your inventory, David. This means Finnegan is heading in alone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
